rComments: Prof is very sweet and understanding. I asked her to move my evaluation date and she accepted right away. However, her exams are very hard and don't really always have to do with class material. Most of her quizzes include material learnt minutes ago in class...

Professor Wirz-Endrys was an absolute sweetheart. Her quizzes were frequent and if you skipped a class, you'd be missing a big portion of course material. She is kind and understanding. Although she does put people on the spot (cameras on), if you can't get the answer right away she will give you hints. If you don't do well, it is entirely on you.

I went in knowing German would be my most difficult class however I didn't expect the workload. Quizzes every week with homework being assigned most weeks. I was made to feel stupid for not knowing the answer to something. Cameras are mandatory which was inconvenient. Overall: attendance is mandatory, unnecessarily judgemental and lots of work.

Awful awful awful. If you are a student registered at SASS avoid this prof. She didnt register any exams on there so if you require accommodations and happen to have any testing the day of exams, you're screwed. Calls you out in class, doesn't let you redeem yourself if you stumble and fails you if she doesn't like what you submit for petty reasons

Professor Brigit is probably the most petty teacher I've ever had. Homework every single class, sometimes gives us only 1 day to complete. She will make sure you get a bad grade despite your test performances if she doesn't like you. She does not know how to use brightspace or set up quizzes and tests. Avoid her if you can. One of the worst at uOtt

I found this professor did not facilitate learning. She calls out students in class to answer questions on material she has just "taught" and makes you feel awful about yourself for making a mistake. She takes a percentage for each missed class, has a quiz every week and is not pleasant towards students during class time. Not worth for an elective.

Actually making an effort to understand the German language and German culture are, rather fittingly, crucial to doing well in her classes. A lot of my peers struggled with this. She does give lots of assignments, keeping the course going at a good pace. Relatively easy to get help from. Nice professor with dry sense of humor. Environmentalist :)

I switched profs so fast. I attended every lecture, and asked a multitude of questions but she is so vague. She refuses to explain in English, give translations, be clear about assignments and tests. She focuses on the smartest and quickest learners(usually those who have previous knowledge) If she is teaching my class next sem I'll drop it IDC.

She doesn't give her students the time to absorb her teachings. She usually focuses on the best students and leaves those who have a hard time behind. Her expectactions regarding assignments are unclear and change on the drop of hat and she will expect you to know everything perfectly for the test, even if she taught the content on the same week.

Do your homework!!! A quiz for each chapter (about 12) Midterm and final are not too hard (if you study) A few oral presentations and written assignments Instructions are always super clear Shes really kind, funny and cares about her students

If you take a little time outside of class to actually practice and do the homework, this class is a breeze. Quiz every week, but it's basically from the workbook. Sometimes not the clearest, but she's an easy, forgiving marker and understands you're a beginner learner. Posts all notes online, and sometimes will call on you to answer questions.

All quizzes are virtually identical to the excercises in the workbook.  I would recommend this course and prof to any science students who want an easy elective. If you're smart this class will bore you to tears because it moves so slowly, but you will get an A. Lots of participation/talking with your classmates/partner work.

Very unclear, note taking turns into a mess. Expects a lot without specifying what's expected. Very hard marker, with tough work. Usually gives last minute additions to assignments and tests. Office hours are extremely unhelpful
Grammar aspect very difficult, and hard to keep up. Lectures varied between very interesting (talking to the class in German conversationally), and draining to follow.
She's a great prof, the class is an easy A+. You must attend class or you will lose 1% per course you miss (she takes prescences)

Currently in her class and I love her. She is very sweet and she seems like she really cares about her students. Makes class interesting. Beware of oral presentations and group work, that's all it is. She gives a quiz each week as well. Overall she's cute and energetic, it was refreshing

Prof. Wirz Endrys is a great professor. Fair amount of homework (usually not checked) and a few assigments. You need to participate in class, which isn't hard considering she's friendly and tries  incorporates audio, vial and written tools to help fully absorb material. Textbook is a must for quizzes (taken from book). Would recommend
Great prof however she doesn't look at the students too often so she never sees students raise their hands when they have questions so that can be kind of annoying.
She's not that clear with course expectations and didn't seem to like answering questions. I liked learning German but would not take her again.

She's very approachable and made the class enjoyable. She really enjoys teaching German and usually has little stories about Germany. Her handouts are very useful and straightforward, but you have to do homework. Like with any language class, you must stay on top of you work and practice. There was a mini quiz every week, but I found they helped

Prof. Endrys is a little tough in the beginning, but if you study, do your homework and participate in class you will do well. She cares if her students show that they are interested in her class, which is not unreasonable. Very nice and helpful if you go see her during her office hours.

Very bad teacher. Does nothing to help you and very critical to everythig. Will take no regards to your comments or opinions and will always put herself as highly superior to you in terms of a human being. If you can, DO NOT take her.

Does not show up to office hours. She is unclear of what is expected on quizzes. She will mention something once and next thing you know a whole section of  your testquiz is based on something she said literally once and did not go over. I do not recommend this teacher.

Very difficult prof and very heavy course load. Although she's enthusiastic and loves teaching German, at this level a lot of students get left in the dust. Worked very hard and addressed my learning concerns with her to no avail. Grammar component is very difficult and little time is spent on it. Disappointed overall.

Don't take this class to learn German coz you won't. She doesn't teach grammar enough and that's ALL German is about! She makes you read a LOT which is extremely frustrating when you don't understand a word you're reading. She should explain the grammar rules more and teach us vocabulary. To pass the class though, all you have to do is the homework

Amazing professor with great teaching methods. She's very approachable; you can tell she really cares about her students. She's very nice and laughs a lot. It's never a boring class with her. If you do the homework and show up to class, I guarantee you an A. If you have the choice, take her class!

Great Prof! Likes to have fun in class as long as she can get everything that she had planned for class done. Easy course if you have an interest in learning the language. Tests were simple if you know your stuff. I loved this course!
While nice, her teaching style was not very effective, and she's addicted to overheads that were too small and impossible to read. Easy A if you attend class, but I would not recommend this prof.

Very nice lady, but kind of out of it. She only knew the names of a few students and would call on them for everything. It's very important to go to class. The class is structured but dry. Every day is the exact same with very little variation. All in all, if languages are your thing you'll probably love it. If not, it's SUPER boring.

Overall a fairly good german prof in comparison to some of the other ones around. She certainly knows what she's doing but expects a lot out of her students. Her tests are HARD so study and make sure you review your notes regularily. It's not the bird course everyone believes it to be. Only take it if you have time to review!

Extremely helpful teacher. You need to attend all lectures, discussion groups, and do all the homework. It's easy to get a good mark; however, the class moves very fast so you can't slack at all. There is a lot of forced participation so be prepared, definitely not a class you can just sleep in or not pay attention. Overall is was good.
Great teacher! She's very nice and understanding. Quite clear on the whole. I would take another class with her any time!

Skipped a few classes and had a hard time keeping up after that.. Moves at a fast pace so you must attend all classes and discussion groups if you want to do well in this class (as with all language classes). Very friendly and understanding prof who genuinely cares about her students success.

Loved her! Super nice and sweet and helpful! The class was fun, but don't expect it to be a bird. If you're really interested in learning the language, you're mark will be good. Must go to class and do homework. Honestly such a fun class, I found the tests pretty easy for a language course. She's wonderful! Take her class!
I loved her! I'm looking for her name when taking german again! Funny, but precise. She is very picky so watch out for that. She should be less attatched to her beloved overhead.....LOL

THIS PROF RULES! She is so cute, full of energy and really cares about her students. Definitely the most wonderful prof I've ever had. She makes the class really fun and the oral presentations and tests are very well structured. I'd reccommend this class to anyone.

She's nuts, but it's funny sometimes. The class gets REALLY frustrating and the tests are extremley hard. I definitely agree that she expects WAY too much. I took it hoping it would be a joke class, but I really regret that decision now. The assingments are really easy however, and you sing stupid songs, which can be fun.

she was so nice! a bit unclear sometimes but you just have to think about the new concept on your own until you get it. the tests seemed hard, but when getting the marks back, apparently not! you just must attend ALL classes if possible because she will expect you to know what was covered the next time and if you don't know you look very foolish.

Prog W-E is really nice.  At first she seems intimidating but shes actually really approachable.  Overall I really liked her.  this class is a lot easier if you actually have an interest in the material.  Dont take it just to fill a spot because you wont do well.  But she is interesting and if you understand her sense of humour shes really funny!

I didn't like her at all. Her tests were ridiculous, and you were expected to memorize way too much way too fast. She spent too much time going over and over unimportant things, and expected you to keep up when we had to speed through the difficult parts to try to get back on track. I would not recommend her.
